### Styling Guidelines

#### Tailwind Classes Order

Layout (display, position)
Spacing (margin, padding)
Sizing (width, height)
Typography (font, text)
Colors (background, text color)
Borders
Effects (shadows, opacity)
Animations
Responsive modifiers

#### Custom Styles

Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
Use CSS modules for complex animations
Define design tokens in tailwind.config.js

### 8.1 Design principles

- **Clarity**: Clear visual hierarchy and intuitive navigation
- **Efficiency**: Minimize clicks and streamline workflows
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- **Responsiveness**: Full mobile and tablet support
- **Consistency**: Unified design language across all features

### 8.2 Visual design

- **Color Palette**: Modern emerald and teal with complementary accent colors
  - Primary: Emerald (#10b981) for success states and primary actions
  - Accent: Teal (#14b8a6) for secondary elements and highlights
  - Warning: Amber (#f59e0b) for caution states
  - Error: Red (#ef4444) for error states
  - Neutral: Gray scale for backgrounds and text
- **Typography**: Plus Jakarta Sans for modern, professional appearance
  - Primary font: Plus Jakarta Sans for all UI elements
  - Fallback: Inter, system-ui, sans-serif
  - Monospace: Fira Code, JetBrains Mono for code elements
- **Spacing**: 8px grid system with consistent padding and margins
- **Icons**: Lucide React icon set with semantic meaning
  - Use contextual icons instead of generic shapes
  - Meaningful pictograms for dashboard cards and status indicators
- **Animations**: Subtle transitions and micro-interactions for better UX
  - Standard transitions: 0.3s ease-out
  - Hover effects: subtle scale and color changes
  - Loading states: smooth progress indicators

### 8.3 Key UI components

#### 8.3.1 Dashboard layout

- Fixed header with user menu and search functionality
- Collapsible sidebar (224px/56px expanded, 56px/14px collapsed) for optimized space usage
- Main content area with responsive grid (gap-6 spacing)
- Rounded corners (rounded-xl) for modern appearance
- Subtle borders and shadows for depth without heaviness
- Emerald accent colors for active states and primary actions

#### 8.3.2 Dashboard cards and metrics

- Meaningful pictograms using Lucide icons:
  - BookOpen for exam totals with trending indicators
  - CheckCircle for completion metrics
  - Clock for processing status with time estimates
  - Coins for credit balance with plan information
- Consistent card structure with proper visual hierarchy
- Color-coded backgrounds (emerald-100, amber-100, indigo-100) for icon containers
- Performance indicators and contextual information below main metrics

#### 8.3.3 Exam creation wizard

- Step progress indicator with emerald theme
- Clear CTAs for navigation with consistent button styling
- Auto-save functionality indicator
- Help tooltips for complex fields
- Proper form validation with emerald success states

#### 8.3.4 Results interface

- Tab-based navigation for different views
- Interactive charts using Recharts with emerald color scheme
- Expandable student result cards with proper spacing
- Inline editing capabilities with focus states

#### 8.3.5 Mobile experience

- Bottom navigation for key actions
- Swipe gestures for navigation
- Optimized file upload flow
- Responsive data tables with proper mobile breakpoints
- Collapsible sidebar transforms to overlay on mobile

### 8.4 Accessibility features

- Keyboard navigation support with proper focus indicators
- Screen reader compatibility with semantic HTML
- High contrast mode option
- Sufficient color contrast ratios (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Alt text for all images and icons
- ARIA labels for interactive elements
- Meaningful icon usage with text labels when needed

### 8.5 Component styling standards

#### Cards and containers
- Use rounded-xl for modern appearance
- Consistent shadow-sm with subtle borders (border-gray-100)
- Proper padding (p-6 for cards, p-3/p-4 for smaller containers)
- Background: white with subtle gray borders

#### Buttons and interactive elements
- Primary: emerald theme (bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700)
- Secondary: gray theme with emerald accents
- Proper sizing with consistent padding
- Hover states with subtle transitions

#### Typography hierarchy
- Headings: Bold weights with proper sizing (text-3xl, text-xl, text-lg)
- Body text: Regular weight with good line height
- Secondary text: Gray-600 for reduced emphasis
- Consistent font-medium for labels and important text

### 8.6 Internationalization

- Support for RTL languages
- Locale-specific number formatting
- Date/time localization
- Translatable UI strings
- Cultural considerations in design
- Icon directionality awareness